channel.title: Port in use problem
channel.description: i recently downloaded a 614 client and tried it with their source, but the source is very hard to figure out and has nothing. i tried running my source and i got an error saying that the port is already in use but nothing is using it. the cmd from the other source is closed and does not appear on the task manager...how do i fix this?

item.title: Port in use problem
item.dc:creator: @i0wn3v3ry i0wn3v3ry
item.description:
@i0wn3v3ry wrote:

[quote=“Your Master, post:5, topic:372031”][quote author=rash link=topic=468090.msg3422378#msg3422378 date=1291605436]
are you running utorrent?
[/quote]uTorrent has nothing to do with portforwarding.[/quote]
Yes, it actually does. If you knew anything about port-forwarding, it is an easier way for people who are lazy.
UTorret, allows people to simply run it, and it port-forwards.
If this is running, and THEN he turns on his server, it would cause the server to not RUN.
If he turned on his server, then ran Utorret, it would then work.

Thanks though.
